DIV1.P:
3. The Presence of CHRIST in a House of pub∣lick Worship renders it glorious, as it renders the Sacraments there administred, pleasant, desirable and beneficial. The Sacraments of Christs In∣stitution, are Baptism and the Lord's Supper. These are usually to be administred in Publick, in places set apart for God's worship; but the


influence and the efficacy, the benefit and ad∣vantage of them, depends upon Christ's Spirit ere. The Baptism of Water will not of it elf wash away Sin: That must be done by the enewing of the Holy Ghost, or else the Or∣dinance will be ineffectual. So the spiritual benefit and advantage of the Lord's Supper, is owing to the Presence of the Lord there▪ His Blessing and gracious Presence there, ren∣ders the Ordinance effectual, for the com∣forting and edifying the body of Christ, till we all come in the unity of the faith and of the knowlege of the Son of God, unto a per∣fect man, to the measure of the stature of the fulness of Christ. This renders it pleasant & desirable, as well as advantagious and benefi∣cial. To Sit at the Table of the Lord, this causes his People to sit under his shadow with great delight▪ and makes his fruit sweet to their taste. They are refreshed edified and com∣forted by it, and improved in their fitness for Heavenly Glory▪ Here they receive some foretasts of the inexpressible pleasure of Com∣munion with Christ. This strengthens their hands and encourages their hearts to be sled∣fast & unmoveable, always to abound in the work of the Lord; and causes them to wax stronger and stronger in the Lord and in the power of his Might, and to grow brighter and brighter Ornaments of Christ's Church;


like those the Psalmist speaks of, that are plan∣ted in the house of the Lord, They will flourish in the courts of our God, they'll bring forth fruit in old age, Psal. 92. 13, 14.
